        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 26 at 5:27PM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 527 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Veribest, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Paint Rock, Miles, Mereta, Veribest, Lowake, Rowena, The Intersection
Of Us-83 And Ranch Road 1929, Us-83 Near The Concho-
Runnels County Line, Harriet, and The Intersection Of Ranch Road 380
And Ranch Road 381.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM CDT for west central
Texas.</instruction>
